.DT
mccp
Discworld player help
mccp

.SH Name
.SI 5 mccp - Check to see if you're using MCCP.
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5
MCCP is the Mud Client Compression Protocol.  This command allows you to check 
whether you are connecting to Discworld using MCCP or not.  Using MCCP reduces 
bandwidth use by approximately 20%.  Players using MCCP should experience 
significantly less lag, and will be given priority in login queues. 
.EP

.SP 5 5 
This command also displays the total number of people connecting to Discworld
using MCCP.
.EP

.SH Examples
.SI 5
>mccp
You are currently using MCCP to connect to Discworld.
Eighty-eight users are currently using MCCP.
>mccp
You are not currently using MCCP to connect to Discworld.  Please read 'help compression' for more information about MCCP.
Seventy users are currently using MCCP.
.EP

.SH See also:
.SP 5 5
compression
.EP 